---
description: Best practices and guidelines for Lua 5.1
globs: **/*.lua
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use local variables to limit scope and improve performance
- Prefer `table.concat` over string concatenation in loops
- Utilize coroutines for cooperative multitasking
- Implement error handling with `pcall` and `xpcall`
- Use metatables for object-oriented programming
- Optimize loops by caching table lengths
- Employ `string.format` for string building and formatting
- Leverage closures for data encapsulation and modular code